The 1948 Ford Mercury drove past the watchers of Monroe, Georgia, and digged toward Moore's Ford Bridge.
But before a car with four black-skinned passengers and a white driver could reach the bridge, a group of white men with guns had blocked it.
The leader of the group - a middle-aged man in a striped suit - long pulled from a cigarette and looked at the windshield of a car.
