It needed to develop not only in activism and organization, but at the same time it had to know the difference between different layers of experience with black people and what we had to do to free ourselves.
Although I am able to provide her with conditions in which she will not experience racism on her own, she is no different from any other black child-woman.
I feel that if I could protect her from this experience, I would only harm her. "
On arrival in Ferguson, South Florissant Road was the first stop across the street from the police department, which became the base of the activists who were expecting the words of Officer Darren Wilson about his possible involvement in the incident.
This is where Ferrell and her daughter met a local businessman who prepared food for the others.
Together they prepared food in bags and helped deliver it to Protestants.
In Ferrell's eyes, a new type of activism was slowly born.
"My activism turned upside down after August 9," said Ferrell, and added that she was President of Minority Student Nurses Ass., and sought to introduce health care and food in black communities when studying at the University of Missouri-St. Louis.
"I had no experience with organization.
