Meanwhile, back in Ferguson, the television station cameras have cleared their positions, but the heavy racial ties between the community and the police remain.
Ferrell is serving two and a half years probation for blocking the highway in demonstrations.
She described the social political atmosphere in an area she calls home as "disorder."
Yet she hasn't stopped her efforts, which she committed herself to since she went to the streets of Ferguson three years ago.
"It is our duty to fight for our freedom.
